Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites
from greens. Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
scallion whites and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in
@jasmine rice{3/4%cups}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then
cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.
Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Dice @roma tomato{1}(diced). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). In a
#small bowl{}, combine tomato, scallion greens, a squeeze of lime juice,
and half the lime zest. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice @jalapeño{1}(thinly sliced) into thin rounds, removing ribs and seeds for
less heat. In a second small bowl, combine jalapeño, @hot water{1%tbsp},
@?sugar{½%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), juice from half the lime (whole lime for
4), and a pinch of @salt{}.

In a third small bowl, combine @avocado{4%smushed} guacamole, @sour cream{2}, and
a squeeze of lime juice.

Pat @diced steak{10} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}
. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over high heat.
Once oil is shimmering, add steak and sprinkle with @southwest spice blend{1}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.
> TIP: Lower heat if steak begins to brown too quickly. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in remaining lime zest and season with salt.
Divide between bowls. Top rice with diced steak, salsa, avocado crema, as much
pickled jalapeño as you like, and @monterey jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Serve with
any remaining lime wedges on the side.